## Context Loading

forge hooks automatically inject project context (rules, wiki index, state, backlog,
learnings) at session start and after context compaction. You do not need to manually
load context files. The hooks handle this.

If you need the full structured briefing, run `/recall`.

## Project Rules

Rules in `{{PROJECT_NAME}}-context/RULES.md` are non-negotiable. They are loaded
automatically by hooks. Always follow them. Add new rules with `/rule`.

## Wiki Navigation

The knowledge base lives at `{{PROJECT_NAME}}-context/wiki/`. The INDEX.md (loaded
automatically) is a ~2K token map of all articles.

When you need deep context:
1. Check the INDEX.md already in your context for the relevant article
2. Read that specific article (not the whole wiki)
3. Follow cross-references as needed

When you discover something new about the codebase:
1. Check if a relevant wiki article exists
2. Update it (or create one)
3. Update INDEX.md if you created a new article

The wiki compounds over time. Every session should leave it richer.

